imdb.plot outline: Deborah, one of the most talked about women in the Bible, tells Barak they should take on the Canaanite army. But he worries they don't stand a chance against Canaanite commander Sisera and his modern technology. Deborah assures Barak they've got G-d on their side. As Deborah prophesied, a woman settles the score with Sisera. Judge Deborah, a prophet and warrior, came after Shamgar who followed Ehud in the Book of Judges.
